# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# fracjson (FracturedJson CLI) is the **.NET JSON
# formatter** by j-brooke — reformats JSON documents
# to make them highly human-readable.  Pivots from
# Lua argparse (R285 luacheck) into the **.NET / C#
# language tooling cluster**.  Sister to dotnet CLI,
# Microsoft.dotnet-* tools.  **MAJOR MILESTONE**:
# corpus's **first documented C# System.CommandLine
# CLI** — adds C# to the cross-language CLI taxonomy
# (25 library variants now).
#
# Critical extraction note: fracjson uses **C#'s
# `System.CommandLine`** library — corpus's **first
# documented C# System.CommandLine CLI**.
# `System.CommandLine` is **Microsoft's official .NET
# CLI library** — built into the .NET ecosystem.
# Used by .NET's own CLI tools (dotnet, dotnet-* tools),
# PowerShell command parameters, and most modern C#
# CLI tooling.  Extends the **cross-language CLI
# taxonomy** to TWENTY-FIVE library variants: Rust (6),
# Go (4), Python (3), Crystal OptionParser (R269),
# Haskell optparse-applicative (R270), OCaml Cmdliner
# (R271), C POSIX getopt (R272), Java picocli (R276),
# Kotlin clikt (R277), Scala decline (R278), Dart args
# (R279), Ruby OptionParser (R280), Perl Getopt::Long
# (R281), PHP Symfony Console (R282), Swift
# ArgumentParser (R283), F# Argu (R284), Lua argparse
# (R285), **C# System.CommandLine** (R286 — NEW).
# **MAJOR PATTERN MILESTONE**: 25 cross-language CLI
# library variants documented.  Documents the **C#
# generic-type-parameter CLI declaration pattern**:
# ```csharp
#   private static readonly Option<int?> _lengthOpt =
#       new("--length", "--MaxTotalLineLength", "-l")
#       {
#           Description = "Max characters per line"
#       };
# ```
# Distinct from F# Argu's discriminated-union pattern
# (R284 fsix) — both .NET ecosystem but **C# uses
# generic types** while F# uses sum types.  Documents
# the **.NET CLI library divide**: System.CommandLine
# is for C# / generic-types; Argu is for F# /
# discriminated-unions.
#
# Critical extraction note: fracjson uses **C# OBJECT
# INITIALIZER syntax** at CliParser.cs:186-191,
# 198-203, 206-211 — C#'s `new T(args) { Prop1 = val1,
# Prop2 = val2 }` syntax sets properties after
# construction without calling individual setter
# methods.  Documents the **C# object-initializer
# CLI declaration pattern** — distinct from
# Cmdliner's pipeline syntax (R271 dune), Symfony's
# `addOption` imperative calls (R282 peridot), and
# Swift property wrappers (R283 yap).  C#'s syntax
# is the most CONCISE for setting multiple properties
# on a constructed object.  Corpus's **first
# documented C# object-initializer CLI pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: fracjson uses **multiple
# aliases as constructor positional args** at
# CliParser.cs:213, 229, 232, 235, 238-239, etc. —
# `new Option<bool>("--minify")`, `new Option<int?>
# ("--length", "--MaxTotalLineLength", "-l")` — the
# FIRST positional arg is the canonical name; ALL
# subsequent positional args are aliases.  Documents
# the **constructor-positional-aliases pattern** —
# distinct from Rust clap derive's `#[arg(short, long
# = "...", alias = "...")]` (R250 sozo), Click's
# `@click.option("--long", "-s")` decorator (R266
# uvicorn), and Symfony's separate aliases array (R282
# peridot).  C#'s approach is the MOST COMPACT for
# multiple aliases.  Plus fracjson uses
# **dual-naming-convention** for backward-compat:
# every option has BOTH a kebab-case short name
# (`--length`) AND a PascalCase library name
# (`--MaxTotalLineLength`).  Corpus's **first
# documented dual-naming-convention** for CLI
# backward-compat.
#
# Critical extraction note: fracjson uses **NULLABLE
# generic types** for tri-state options at
# CliParser.cs:248-298 — `Option<bool?>` /
# `Option<int?>` use C#'s `T?` nullable syntax to
# distinguish 3 states: NOT-SET (null) / FALSE / TRUE
# for booleans, or NOT-SET / int value for integers.
# Documents the **nullable-tri-state pattern** in C#
# — distinct from clap derive's `Option<T>` field
# type (R260 dua — uses Rust's `Option`), Swift
# ArgumentParser's `T?` (R283 yap), and Click's
# `default=None` (R266 uvicorn).  All three approach
# the same problem (distinguishing default-not-set
# from explicit-default) but C#'s `T?` is LANGUAGE-
# LEVEL nullable types.  Used by fracjson to allow
# config file values to override defaults: CLI null
# → use config; CLI false → override config with
# false.  Corpus's **first documented C# nullable
# tri-state CLI pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: fracjson uses
# **`DefaultValueFactory = (_ => false)`** at
# CliParser.cs:210 — C# property initializer with a
# LAMBDA EXPRESSION for the default value.  `(_ =>
# false)` is `argResult => false` (ignores arg result,
# returns false).  Documents the **closure-based
# default value factory** pattern in C# — distinct
# from R262 matugen's Rust `default_value = fn()`
# (free fn call), R266 uvicorn's Click `default=False`
# (literal value), and R267 alembic's argparse
# `default=False` (literal value).  C#'s lambda
# allows COMPUTED defaults that can reference the
# parse result.  Plus the `_` is C#'s discard pattern
# for unused parameters.  Corpus's **first
# documented lambda-default-factory pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: fracjson uses **chained
# `.AcceptExistingOnly()`** at CliParser.cs:191 +
# 203 — System.CommandLine's chainable VALIDATOR
# method that requires the file argument to refer
# to an existing file.  Returns the option/argument
# for further chaining.  Documents the **chained-
# validator pattern** in System.CommandLine —
# similar to clap derive's `value_parser` (R248
# cairo-coverage) and Click's `type=click.Path
# (exists=True)` (R266 uvicorn).  Plus System
# .CommandLine ships several stock validators:
# `AcceptExistingOnly` (file exists),
# `AcceptOnlyFromAmong(values)` (restricted values).
#
# Critical extraction note: fracjson uses **C#
# COLLECTION INITIALIZER syntax** for RootCommand at
# CliParser.cs:300-333 — `new RootCommand(description)
# { opt1, opt2, opt3, ... }` adds all listed
# options/arguments to the root command via C#'s
# `IEnumerable.Add` pattern.  System.CommandLine's
# RootCommand implements `IEnumerable` so the
# initializer-list syntax calls `Add(opt)` for each
# element.  Documents the **collection-initializer
# RootCommand pattern** — distinct from Symfony
# Console's array-of-Definition (R282 peridot) and
# Swift ArgumentParser's `subcommands:` array (R283
# yap).  C#'s approach is unique in REPURPOSING the
# collection-initializer syntax for CLI declaration.
# Corpus's **first documented collection-initializer
# CLI declaration**.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line

# Enum values from FracturedJson library.
local -a eol_styles=(LF CRLF)
local -a number_alignments=(Decimal Left Right Normalize)
local -a table_commas=(BeforeValue AfterValue None)
local -a comment_policies=(Preserve Remove TreatAsError)

# 30+ options decoded source-direct from CliParser.cs
# lines 194-298.  Most options have DUAL-NAMING-
# CONVENTION: kebab-case + PascalCase aliases.
_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help (System.CommandLine HelpOption)]' \
  '(--version)--version[show version (System.CommandLine VersionOption)]' \
  '(--no-config)--config=[FracturedJsonOptions config file (mutex with --no-config; AcceptExistingOnly)]:file:_files -g "*.json"' \
  '(--config)--no-config[ignore config file; use only CLI / defaults]' \
  '(-o --output-file)'{-o+,--output-file=}'[write output to file (overwrites if exists)]:file:_files' \
  '--minify[output compact/minified JSON (overrides most formatting)]' \
  '--time[write elapsed formatting time to stdout]' \
  '--wide[adjust display width for East Asian (CJK) wide characters]' \
  '(--eol --JsonEolStyle)--eol=[line ending style]:style:($eol_styles)' \
  '(--eol --JsonEolStyle)--JsonEolStyle=[alias for --eol (dual-naming PascalCase)]:style:($eol_styles)' \
  '(-l --length --MaxTotalLineLength)'{-l+,--length=}'[max chars per line including indent]:n:' \
  '(-l --length --MaxTotalLineLength)--MaxTotalLineLength=[alias for --length]:n:' \
  '(-i --inline --MaxInlineComplexity)'{-i+,--inline=}'[max nesting depth allowed inline on one line]:n:' \
  '(-i --inline --MaxInlineComplexity)--MaxInlineComplexity=[alias for --inline]:n:' \
  '(-a --array --MaxCompactArrayComplexity)'{-a+,--array=}'[max nesting for compact arrays]:n:' \
  '(-a --array --MaxCompactArrayComplexity)--MaxCompactArrayComplexity=[alias for --array]:n:' \
  '(-t --table --MaxTableRowComplexity)'{-t+,--table=}'[max nesting for table-style formatting]:n:' \
  '(-t --table --MaxTableRowComplexity)--MaxTableRowComplexity=[alias for --table]:n:' \
  '(--prop-padding --MaxPropNamePadding)--prop-padding=[max spaces to line up property values]:n:' \
  '(--prop-padding --MaxPropNamePadding)--MaxPropNamePadding=[alias for --prop-padding]:n:' \
  '(--colon-before --ColonBeforePropNamePadding)--colon-before[colon BEFORE property-name padding]' \
  '(--colon-before --ColonBeforePropNamePadding)--ColonBeforePropNamePadding[alias for --colon-before]' \
  '(--table-comma --TableCommaPlacement)--table-comma=[comma position in table rows]:placement:($table_commas)' \
  '(--table-comma --TableCommaPlacement)--TableCommaPlacement=[alias for --table-comma]:placement:($table_commas)' \
  '(--min-array-items --MinCompactArrayRowItems)--min-array-items=[minimum items per row for compact arrays]:n:' \
  '(--min-array-items --MinCompactArrayRowItems)--MinCompactArrayRowItems=[alias for --min-array-items]:n:' \
  '(--always-expand --AlwaysExpandDepth)--always-expand=[force expansion from root to depth (-1 = no force)]:n:' \
  '(--always-expand --AlwaysExpandDepth)--AlwaysExpandDepth=[alias for --always-expand]:n:' \
  '(--nested-pad --NestedBracketPadding)--nested-pad[space inside complex bracket containers]' \
  '(--nested-pad --NestedBracketPadding)--NestedBracketPadding[alias for --nested-pad]' \
  '(--simple-pad --SimpleBracketPadding)--simple-pad[space inside simple bracket containers]' \
  '(--simple-pad --SimpleBracketPadding)--SimpleBracketPadding[alias for --simple-pad]' \
  '(--colon-pad --ColonPadding)--colon-pad[space after colon]' \
  '(--colon-pad --ColonPadding)--ColonPadding[alias for --colon-pad]' \
  '(--comma-pad --CommaPadding)--comma-pad[space after comma]' \
  '(--comma-pad --CommaPadding)--CommaPadding[alias for --comma-pad]' \
  '(--comment-pad --CommentPadding)--comment-pad[space between comment and value]' \
  '(--comment-pad --CommentPadding)--CommentPadding[alias for --comment-pad]' \
  '(--number-align --NumberListAlignment)--number-align=[number column alignment]:alignment:($number_alignments)' \
  '(--number-align --NumberListAlignment)--NumberListAlignment=[alias for --number-align]:alignment:($number_alignments)' \
  '(--indent --IndentSpaces)--indent=[spaces per indent level]:n:' \
  '(--indent --IndentSpaces)--IndentSpaces=[alias for --indent]:n:' \
  '(--tabs --UseTabToIndent)--tabs[use tabs instead of spaces for indent]' \
  '(--tabs --UseTabToIndent)--UseTabToIndent[alias for --tabs]' \
  '(--prefix --PrefixString)--prefix=[prefix every output line with this string]:string:' \
  '(--prefix --PrefixString)--PrefixString=[alias for --prefix]:string:' \
  '(-c --comments --CommentPolicy)'{-c+,--comments=}'[how to handle // or /* comments]:policy:($comment_policies)' \
  '(-c --comments --CommentPolicy)--CommentPolicy=[alias for --comments]:policy:($comment_policies)' \
  '(--blanks --PreserveBlankLines)--blanks[keep blank lines from input]' \
  '(--blanks --PreserveBlankLines)--PreserveBlankLines[alias for --blanks]' \
  '(--trailing --AllowTrailingCommas)--trailing[permit trailing commas in arrays/objects from input]' \
  '(--trailing --AllowTrailingCommas)--AllowTrailingCommas[alias for --trailing]' \
  '*:input JSON file (reads stdin if omitted; AcceptExistingOnly):_files -g "*.(json|jsonc)"'
